race.comment: AUTUMN GLOW (7) returns in the G2 Apollo as the unbeaten rising star of the turf, and everything suggests she's ready to keep the streak alive. Two hit-outs have her screwed down and the 1400m is an ideal launchpad. The map allows McDonald to slide across from the wide draw and stalk the speed. Short quote to go 9/9. STEFI MAGNETICA (8) has trialled every bit as sharply as she can and should follow AUTUMN GLOW across. She's electric on her day and is the one capable of landing a real blow if the big guns get too cute. LINDERMANN (3) embodies grit and went to a new level in the spring with several elite efforts. He'll spear straight to the front and make them earn it. CEOLWULF (1) ended the spring in career-best touch, claiming the King Charles and Champions Mile. His fresh record is the only knock, but he commands respect. AELIANA (9) was terrific fresh here in the spring when beaten a long neck by Via Sistina in the G1 Winx, though the setup here may leave her with too much to do.
